The paper deals with natural language generation and language style transfer, which are core topics in computational linguistics (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The authors also use machine learning techniques such as supervised learning and evaluate their results using BLEU score, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and deep learning (cs.DL). Finally, the paper applies its approach to famous paintings, which suggests a potential application in computer vision (cs.CV).
